The paper discusses the orchestration of network services, which involves the coordination of network, storage, and compute resources across heterogeneous infrastructures and administrative domains. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, including network infrastructure (cs.NI), software-defined networking (cs.SD), data centers (cs.DC), distributed systems (cs.DS), and software engineering (cs.SE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
